<h1>Module 5:</h1>
<h2>Loops and the DOM</h2>

<p>My Favorite cars are:</p>
<p id="demo1"></p>
<p>But my dream car is:</p>
<p id="p1">
Nissan GT-R
</p>

<input type="button" value="Hide text" 
onclick="document.getElementById('p1').style.visibility='hidden'">
<input type="button" value="Show text"
onclick="document.getElementById('p1').style.visibility='visible'">

<script>
const cars = ["F-150 King Ranch", "GT-R", "Shelby Cobra", "Mustang Dark Horse"];
let text = "";
for (let i = 0; i < cars.length; i++) {
  text += cars[i] + "<br>";
};
document.getElementById("demo1").innerHTML = text;
</script>

<h2>JavaScript While Loop - I Can't fuure out how to run two scripts on the same page... =o(</h2>

<p id="demo2"></p>
<script>
let text = "";
let i = 0;
while (i < 10) {
  text += "<br>The number is " + i;
  i++;
}
document.getElementById("demo2").innerHTML = text;
</script>
